Adrian,

as a first step towards resolving your "Block", would you agree if we copy
the current definitions of Constrained Node, Constrained Network and
Constrained Node Network from the LWIG draft into the charter, instead of
citing the draft or referring to the LWIG work in general?

Best regards
Ulrich


On Sun, Sep 1, 2013 at 10:53 AM, Adrian Farrel <adrian@olddog.co.uk> wrote:

> All, ****
>
> ** **
>
> I really want to get out of the way of this work.****
>
> ** **
>
> I understand that the proposed wording:****
>
> - does not preclude the necessary work being done in 6man****
>
> - does not stop any of the intended work being done in 6lo****
>
> ** **
>
> Both of these are good objectives.****
>
> ** **
>
> My concern is that the wording does not prevent other work being done in
> 6lo that has not been dreamed of and would be out of scope if we could
> dream of it.****
>
> I am probably *way* too paranoid, but I am trying to find a form that
> scopes in the work you want to do *and* scopes out the work you have no
> intention of doing.****
>
> ** **
>
> Happy to hear any other suggestions.****
>
> Thanks,****
>
> Adrian****
>
> ** **
>
> *From:* Ulrich Herberg [mailto:ulrich@herberg.name]
