<body lang=3D"EN-US" link=3D"#0563C1" vlink=3D"#954F72">
<div class=3D"WordSection1">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">I attended the 6lo BOF that discussed <span style=3D=
"color:black">
IPv6 over networks of resource-constrained nodes. This was a WG-forming BOF=
, and it was explained that this BOF is sort of a successor to the half-clo=
sed (draining output queue, no input) 6lowpan WG which I understood was sco=
ped to a particular link technology
 (802.15.4).&nbsp; The 6lo BOF on the other hand discussed applicability of=
 the same protocol solutions to other similar link types (</span><span styl=
e=3D"color:black">G.9959, RS485, etc.)</span><span style=3D"color:black">.&=
nbsp; There seemed to be general agreement that
 the 6lowpan mechanisms include a number of modules, and those modules coul=
d be individually reused.&nbsp; There was a question about whether an archi=
tectural description would be in scope, and there seemed to be general agre=
ement to not do so in the proposed WG,
 but rather only refer to what 6lowpan already did.&nbsp; That seems like a=
 good idea to me as long as all the link types that 6lo would do are very s=
imilar to 802.15.4. That is, I think it might be good to scope a 6lo WG as =
such.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">One of the scope discuss=
ions in the BOF was about the use of the term &#8220;constrained node netwo=
rk&#8221; throughout the proposed charter and what that was (e.g., I asked =
if a carrier pigeon network was one :)&nbsp;&nbsp; The LWIG
 WG has a <a href=3D"http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-lwig-terminology=
">terminology doc</a> that defines it, and it was agreed to incorporate the=
 definition into the proposed charter.&nbsp;&nbsp; Another aspect of the sc=
ope discussion was the relationship between
 this BOF and what is in scope of 6man (other IP-over-Foo mechanisms), wher=
e the proposed 6lo charter makes &#8220;constrained node networks&#8221; in=
 scope for 6lo and leaves the rest for 6man.&nbsp;&nbsp; My own take is tha=
t I agree with the goal to keep architectural impact out
 of 6lo (but in 6man instead) and as such, 6lo should be scoped to things w=
here the architecture doesn&#8217;t change from existing RFCs (whether 6low=
pan&#8217;s architectural model or the Ethernet architectural model).&nbsp;=
 This is narrower than the definition of &#8220;constrained
 node network&#8221;.&nbsp; If the scope is really &#8220;constrained node =
network&#8221; then I don&#8217;t think they can (or should) avoid a discus=
sion of architectural model whenever someone comes in with a doc on a &#822=
0;constrained node network&#8221; that can&#8217;t completely emulate Ether=
net
 or 6lowpan&#8217;s model.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">At the end of the BOF, t=
he chairs poll the room on a number of questions:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level=
1 lfo1"><![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"color:black"><span style=3D"mso=
-list:Ignore">1)<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D"color:black">Should the IETF =
address a problem here? &nbsp;There was strong support for yes.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level=
1 lfo1"><![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"color:black"><span style=3D"mso=
-list:Ignore">2)<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D"color:black">Do folks agree w=
ith the proposed charter (with some mods as discussed during the meeting)?&=
nbsp; Again strong support for yes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level=
1 lfo1"><![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"color:black"><span style=3D"mso=
-list:Ignore">3)<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D"color:black">Are there people=
 willing to do work?&nbsp;&nbsp; There were 30-ish hands for willing to com=
ment on docs.&nbsp; There were 10-ish hands for willing to edit docs.&nbsp;=
 There were 25-ish hands for willing to implement docs.<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">So it seemed to me that =
this is about ready to form a WG, and the next step for the IESG is to deci=
de an appropriate scope.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">-Dave<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
</div>
</body>
</html>

