Hi Robert,

Your point is taken. We also heard from Adrian and his suggestions:

"I *do* believe that explicitly stating the definition of Constrained Things
in the charter text will be a very positive step. 
But please understand that, per my Discuss on the LWIG terminology I-D, I
find the definition of a constrained node in that document rather poor."


So, it looks like we have to do some more work on the definition of
"Constrained" nodes and networks  in order to make a progress.

Thanks,
-Samita



