Hi,

I think you have hit on a key point. The LWIG document appears to make an a=
ttempt to redefine the concept of constrained node, and that runs up agains=
t existing definitions.

Actually, that may be harsh! LWIG is trying to define the term, and (as you=
 note) previous usages have been somewhat vague. Unfortunately (IMHO) the a=
ttempt in LWIG to meet the challenge head on has resulted in a rather vague=
 definition.

We could:
a. Work together on the LWIG definition and then re-use it for the 6lo char=
ter
b. Come up with a concise definition for the 6lo charter

I think b) would be faster and better.

Looking at the definition in ROLL I find draft-ietf-roll-terminology that s=
ays "An LLN is typically composed of many embedded devices with limited pow=
er, memory, and processing resources interconnected by a variety of links."=
 That would certainly cover it (there is nothing specific about routing in =
that definition), but it might also be nice to replace "a variety of links"=
 with something a bit more specific. That would cut into my other concern a=
bout which (or what type of) links this work is intended to cover.

Cheers,
Adrian

